verbose_text: A series of high-quality M 2 (BDC) 2 (DABCO) metal-organic frameworks (abbreviated as M-DABCO; M = Zn, Co, Ni, Cu; BDC = 1,4-benzene dicarboxylate; DABCO = 1,4-diazabicyclo [2.2.2] octane), were synthesized by using a solvothermal (SV) method, and their catalytic activity for the cycloaddition of CO 2 to epoxides in the absence of a co-catalyst or solvent was demonstrated.
